      "note": "Sc., \"because they run counter to the idolatrous beliefs which you have inherited from your ancestors\". The story of Noah, briefly mentioned in verses 71-73, is told at greater length in 11:36-48 (see also 7:59-64). Here it connects with verse 47 above, and thus with the main theme of this surah: the truth of God's revelation of His will through His prophets, and the suffering which in the life to come is bound to befall those who give the lie to His messages."
